    <body.head>
      <hedline>
        <hl1>The Estate Tax: Don't Tread on Me</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Bruce Neuman letter on Bob Herbert's June 26 column calls for repeal of estate tax</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Bob Herbert refers to the current legislation to repeal the estate tax as a handout for the wealthy (column, June 26).</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Bob Herbert refers to the current legislation to repeal the estate tax as a handout for the wealthy (column, June 26).</p>
        <p>It is a liberal notion (and I consider myself a liberal) that there is a war between rich and poor in America. In America there is the chance, though small, for both rich and poor to acquire assets. Both the wealthy and the not-so-wealthy agree that you and your family should be able to hold on to what you acquire.</p>
        <p>The estate tax is unpopular in America. Replace the lost revenue with other kinds of taxes on the rich, but get rid of this dinosaur.</p>
        <p>BRUCE NEUMAN  Bridgehampton, N.Y., June 26, 2000</p>
      </block>
